{"$schema":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/3a361e0bc07860055a926e0d41df405c6f0eb3d4/Documents/CommitteeSpecifications/2.1.0/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json","version":"2.1.0","runs":[{"tool":{"driver":{"name":"appScreener","organization":"Solar appScreener","product":"appScreener","fullName":"Solar appScreener","version":"3.15.2","notifications":[],"rules":[{"id":"PYTHON_PASSWORD_HARDCODED","deprecatedIds":[],"deprecatedGuids":[],"name":"Hardcoded password","deprecatedNames":[],"fullDescription":{"text":"<p>Password is hardcoded. This may lead to an application data compromise.</p>\n\n<p>Eliminating security risks related to hardcoded passwords is extremely difficult. These passwords are at least accessible to every developer of the application. Moreover, after the application is installed, removing password from its code is possible only via an update. Constant strings are easily extracted from the compiled application by decompilers. Therefore, an attacker does not necessarily need to have an access to the source code to know the parameters of the special account. If these parameters become known to an attacker, system administrators will be forced either to neglect the safety, or to restrict the access to the application.</p>","markdown":"<p>Password is hardcoded. This may lead to an application data compromise.</p>\n\n<p>Eliminating security risks related to hardcoded passwords is extremely difficult. These passwords are at least accessible to every developer of the application. Moreover, after the application is installed, removing password from its code is possible only via an update. Constant strings are easily extracted from the compiled application by decompilers. Therefore, an attacker does not necessarily need to have an access to the source code to know the parameters of the special account. If these parameters become known to an attacker, system administrators will be forced either to neglect the safety, or to restrict the access to the application.</p>"},"help":{"text":"<ul>\n<li>Store not passwords but values of cryptographically secure hash function from the password. Use specialized hash functions designed for this purpose (bcrypt, scrypt). Use salt obtained from cryptographically secure pseudorandom number generator to resist attacks which use rainbow tables.</li>\n<li>If the hardcoded password is used for the initial authorization, provide the special authentication mode for this purpose in which the user is required to provide his/her own unique password.</li>\n<li>Store authentication information in an encrypted form in a separate configuration file or in a database. Secure the encryption key. If encryption is not possible, limit the access to the repository as much as possible.</li>\n</ul>","markdown":"<ul>\n<li>Store not passwords but values of cryptographically secure hash function from the password. Use specialized hash functions designed for this purpose (bcrypt, scrypt). Use salt obtained from cryptographically secure pseudorandom number generator to resist attacks which use rainbow tables.</li>\n<li>If the hardcoded password is used for the initial authorization, provide the special authentication mode for this purpose in which the user is required to provide his/her own unique password.</li>\n<li>Store authentication information in an encrypted form in a separate configuration file or in a database. Secure the encryption key. If encryption is not possible, limit the access to the repository as much as possible.</li>\n</ul>"},"relationships":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"x-example":"<p>In the following example, a password is hardcoded:</p>\n\n<pre><code>password = &quot;hardcoded&quot;\n</code></pre>","x-classifications":{"cwe":["CWE-256","CWE-257","CWE-259","CWE-522","CWE-656","CWE-798","CWE-862"],"masvs":["2.2","2.14","8.11"],"asvs":["6.4.2","6.4.1","2.10.4","2.4.1","2.4.2","2.4.3","2.4.4","2.4.5"],"pcsdss":["6.5.6","6.2.4","8.3.2","8.6"],"cwesans21":["21","16","18"],"owasp21":["A2","A4","A7"],"hipaa":["§164.312 (a)(1)"],"cwesans23":["18","11"],"owasp17":["A2","A3","A6"]},"x-links":"<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://owasp.org/www-community/vulnerabilities/Use_of_hard-coded_password\">Use of hard-coded password</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/259.html\">CWE-259: Use of Hard-coded Password</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://css.csail.mit.edu/6.858/2014/readings/owasp-top-10.pdf\">OWASP Top 10 2013-A5-Security Misconfiguration</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://css.csail.mit.edu/6.858/2014/readings/owasp-top-10.pdf\">OWASP Top 10 2013-A6-Sensitive Data Exposure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12937641/handling-passwords-used-for-auth-in-source-code\">Handling passwords used for auth in source code - stackoverflow.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://security.stackexchange.com/questions/211/how-to-securely-hash-passwords\">How to securely hash passwords? - security.stackexchange.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/OWASP_Top_Ten_2017/Top_10-2017_A2-Broken_Authentication\">OWASP Top 10 2017 A2-Broken Authentication</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/OWASP_Top_Ten_2017/Top_10-2017_A3-Sensitive_Data_Exposure\">OWASP Top 10 2017-A3-Sensitive Data Exposure</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html\">CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1028.html\">CWE CATEGORY: OWASP Top Ten 2017 Category A2 - Broken Authentication</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1032.html\">CWE CATEGORY: OWASP Top Ten 2017 Category A6 - Security Misconfiguration</a></li>\n</ol>"}},{"id":"PYTHON_DOS","deprecatedIds":[],"deprecatedGuids":[],"name":"DOS attack possible","deprecatedNames":[],"fullDescription":{"text":"<p>DOS-attack is possible. An attacker can submit specially designed values to the application input, which will cause a large amount of computation and can disrupt the normal operation of the application.</p>\n\n<p>Traditional DOS-attack in which the attacker makes a huge number of requests to the application are easy to prevent at network level. The attacks that are more dangerous are ones related to the insecure application logic allowing to disrupt its work with a small amount of specially designed requests. In particular, the application functionality where the user determines the amount of time or system resources used to process his/her request is dangerous.</p>","markdown":"<p>DOS-attack is possible. An attacker can submit specially designed values to the application input, which will cause a large amount of computation and can disrupt the normal operation of the application.</p>\n\n<p>Traditional DOS-attack in which the attacker makes a huge number of requests to the application are easy to prevent at network level. The attacks that are more dangerous are ones related to the insecure application logic allowing to disrupt its work with a small amount of specially designed requests. In particular, the application functionality where the user determines the amount of time or system resources used to process his/her request is dangerous.</p>"},"help":{"text":"<ul>\n<li>Implement a validation mechanism for user-supplied data. This will not allow an attacker to abuse the provided application resources.</li>\n<li>Limit the maximum amount of resources allocated for the processing of one request.</li>\n</ul>","markdown":"<ul>\n<li>Implement a validation mechanism for user-supplied data. This will not allow an attacker to abuse the provided application resources.</li>\n<li>Limit the maximum amount of resources allocated for the processing of one request.</li>\n</ul>"},"relationships":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"x-example":"<p>In the following example, the user can define the parameter of the <code>time.sleep()</code> method:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import time\ntime.sleep(delay)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For large values of <code>delay</code> corresponding thread will stop operating for a considerable period of time.</p>","x-classifications":{"cwe":["CWE-400"],"asvs":["12.1.1"]},"x-links":"<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.owasp.org/index.php/Application_Denial_of_Service\">OWASP: Application Denial of Service</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3.5/library/time.html\">time - Time access and conversions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/400.html\">CWE-400</a></li>\n</ol>"}},{"id":"PYTHON_BACKDOOR_NETWORK_ACTIVITY","deprecatedIds":[],"deprecatedGuids":[],"name":"Undocumented feature: network activity","deprecatedNames":[],"fullDescription":{"text":"<p>The application initiates a connection with the hardcoded external server. If the address is not in the white list, this may indicate undocumented network activity.</p>\n\n<p>Undocumented network activity may lead to a sensitive data exposure. Sensitive Data Exposure takes the third place in the OWASP Top 10 2017 web application vulnerabilities ranking.</p>","markdown":"<p>The application initiates a connection with the hardcoded external server. If the address is not in the white list, this may indicate undocumented network activity.</p>\n\n<p>Undocumented network activity may lead to a sensitive data exposure. Sensitive Data Exposure takes the third place in the OWASP Top 10 2017 web application vulnerabilities ranking.</p>"},"help":{"text":"<ul>\n<li>If the application is trying to connect to the address which is not in the white list, remove the sections of code which use the suspicious connection.</li>\n</ul>","markdown":"<ul>\n<li>If the application is trying to connect to the address which is not in the white list, remove the sections of code which use the suspicious connection.</li>\n</ul>"},"relationships":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"x-example":"<p>In the following example, the application connects to the server with the specified IP address:</p>\n\n<pre><code>urllib2.urlopen('http://79.174.66.120')\n</code></pre>","x-classifications":{"cwe":["CWE-506","CWE-510"],"asvs":["10.2.1"],"pcsdss":["2.2.4"]},"x-links":"<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/506.html\">CWE-506: Embedded Malicious Code</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Backdoor_(computing)\">Backdoor (computing) - Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20200914012723/https://medium.com/asecuritysite-when-bob-met-alice/the-art-of-the-backdoor-e39f001ea8b9\">The Art of the Backdoor</a></li>\n</ol>"}}],"taxa":[],"locations":[],"language":"en-US","contents":["localizedData","nonLocalizedData"],"isComprehensive":false,"supportedTaxonomies":[]},"extensions":[]},"invocations":[],"language":"en-US","versionControlProvenance":[],"artifacts":[],"logicalLocations":[],"graphs":[],"results":[{"ruleId":"PYTHON_DOS","ruleIndex":-1,"kind":"fail","level":"warning","message":{"text":"DOS attack possible","arguments":[]},"locations":[{"id":-1,"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"src/data_processing.py","index":-1},"region":{"startLine":9,"startColumn":15,"endLine":9,"charOffset":-1,"byteOffset":-1,"snippet":{"text":"    \"\"\"\n    Выполняет GET-запрос к публичному API.\n    Эта функция использует библиотеку 'requests' версии 2.26.0,\n    которая имеет известные уязвимости.\n    \"\"\"\n    response = requests.get(\"https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1\")\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    data = response.json()\n    # Простая обработка: берем только нужные поля\n    processed = {\"userId\": data[\"userId\"], \"title\": data[\"title\"]}\n    return processed"}}},"logicalLocations":[],"annotations":[],"relationships":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"x-severity":2}}],"stacks":[],"codeFlows":[],"graphs":[],"graphTraversals":[],"relatedLocations":[],"suppressions":[],"rank":-1.0,"attachments":[],"workItemUris":[],"fixes":[],"taxa":[]},{"ruleId":"PYTHON_PASSWORD_HARDCODED","ruleIndex":-1,"kind":"fail","level":"error","message":{"text":"Hardcoded password","arguments":[]},"locations":[{"id":-1,"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"src/__init__.py","index":-1},"region":{"startLine":6,"startColumn":0,"endLine":6,"charOffset":-1,"byteOffset":-1,"snippet":{"text":"# for gitleaks test\n\n# moved to vault\n# moved to vault\n\nmy_password='Thi$IsP@ssword'"}}},"logicalLocations":[],"annotations":[],"relationships":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"x-severity":3,"x-trace":[{"position":0,"source":"src/__init__.py","lineStart":6,"lineEnd":6,"columnStart":0,"columnEnd":null,"description":"my_password","snippet":"# for gitleaks test\n\n# moved to vault\n# moved to vault\n\nmy_password='Thi$IsP@ssword'"},{"position":1,"source":"src/__init__.py","lineStart":6,"lineEnd":6,"columnStart":12,"columnEnd":null,"description":"'Thi$IsP@ssword'","snippet":"# for gitleaks test\n\n# moved to vault\n# moved to vault\n\nmy_password='Thi$IsP@ssword'"}]}}],"stacks":[],"codeFlows":[],"graphs":[],"graphTraversals":[],"relatedLocations":[],"suppressions":[],"rank":-1.0,"attachments":[],"workItemUris":[],"fixes":[],"taxa":[]},{"ruleId":"PYTHON_BACKDOOR_NETWORK_ACTIVITY","ruleIndex":-1,"kind":"fail","level":"warning","message":{"text":"Undocumented feature: network activity","arguments":[]},"locations":[{"id":-1,"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"src/data_processing.py","index":-1},"region":{"startLine":9,"startColumn":15,"endLine":9,"charOffset":-1,"byteOffset":-1,"snippet":{"text":"    \"\"\"\n    Выполняет GET-запрос к публичному API.\n    Эта функция использует библиотеку 'requests' версии 2.26.0,\n    которая имеет известные уязвимости.\n    \"\"\"\n    response = requests.get(\"https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1\")\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    data = response.json()\n    # Простая обработка: берем только нужные поля\n    processed = {\"userId\": data[\"userId\"], \"title\": data[\"title\"]}\n    return processed"}}},"logicalLocations":[],"annotations":[],"relationships":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"x-severity":1}}],"stacks":[],"codeFlows":[],"graphs":[],"graphTraversals":[],"relatedLocations":[],"suppressions":[],"rank":-1.0,"attachments":[],"workItemUris":[],"fixes":[],"taxa":[]}],"runAggregates":[],"redactionTokens":[],"newlineSequences":["\r\n","\n"],"threadFlowLocations":[],"taxonomies":[],"addresses":[],"translations":[],"policies":[],"webRequests":[],"webResponses":[]}],"inlineExternalProperties":[],"properties":{"tags":[],"rulesVersion":"3.15.1.5e059565"}}